Ethiopia shines as a prime destination for trade and investment, ranking top 5 in Africa for FDI. Recent tech partnerships with giants like Google, Meta, Databricks, & Palantir showcase our welcoming business climate. Exciting expansions and development  in aviation, IT & AI, and workforce development and opportunities abound across sectors like textiles, mining, finance and telecom make Ethiopia a priority destination for FDI.

On March 14/2024, I was blessed and honored to meet with Eminents Archbishops and Leaders of seven archdioceses of the Ethiopian Orthodox Tewahedo Curch in North America. The delegation was led by His Grace Abune Theophilus, Archbishop of the archdiocese in North California and Member of the Holy Synod of the Ethiopian Orthodox Tewahedo Church. We discussed issues of concerns raised by the Church leaders and I have promised to present these concerns to the government and communicate results including forging closer ties for peace and unity of Ethiopia.

Earlier in the week:

- Honored to meet with Congressman Hon. John James, Chair of the African Subcommittee in the House Foreign Relation. I have briefed the congressman, among others, the situation and progresses of CoHA and implementation of peace agreement related to conflict in Northern Ethiopia, humanitarian assistance needed for natural disaster and conflicts, exclusion of Ethiopia from AGOA and its negative impact on jobs, women & young people livelihoods and investors.

- I was pleased to welcome HE Alfredo Nuvunga, Ambassador of Mozambique to our Embassy. We discussed on issues of our two countries bilateral relations, common challenges and mutual interests such as pan African agenda, agriculture productivity, development infrastructure, natural disaster and conflicts. Before his appointment to the USA, HE Ambassador Nuvunga, was Ambassador to Ethiopia and the African Union.

Earlier in the week, I had the honour to meet various US officials and institutional leaders and Ethiopian community:
- State Department officials including Special Envoy on the Horn of Africa Ambassador Hammer and Deputy Asssistant Secretary Peter Lord
- ⁠Senator Warner (D-VA)
- John Tomaszweski, ⁠Senate Foriegn Relation Senior advisor for Ranking Member James E. Risch (R-ID)

Our discussions covered issues of AGOA, conflict and peacemaking measures, Ethiopia’s access to sea, recurring drought and forthcoming AU summit

The wonderful opportunity to meet with the Rockefeller Foundation’s Vice Presidents Eileen O’Connor and Danielle Geanacopoulos accorded me possibility to discuss various potential collaboration in food production and productivity, global energy alliance and renewable energy in Ethiopia

Embassy Staffs and I had also a webinar based candid discussion with about 18 distinguished Ethiopian origin professors on yesterday related to peace, justice and development in Ethiopia.

Ethiopia welcomes the decision by the USAID on resumption of the food assistance to the vulnerable people in Ethiopia.  In consultation with USAID and other stakeholders, Ethiopia has taken reform measures for enhanced aid delivery system. 
There are enormous needs for such support due to natural and manmade vulnerabilities such as drought, flood, displacements and refugees coming across the borders.  

የአሜሪካ ተራድኦ ድርጅት (USAID) በኢትዮጵያ ለእርዳታ ፈላጊዎች የሚሰጠውን የምግብ እርዳታ እንደገና ለማስጀመር ያሳለፈውን ውሳኔ አገራችን በደስታ ትቀበላለች። ኢትዮጵያ ከUSAID እና ከሌሎች ባለድርሻ አካላት ጋር በመመካከር የተሻሻለ የዕርዳታ አሰጣጥ ስርዓትን የማሻሻያ እርምጃዎችን ወስዳለች።

The 3rd  round of two days of intensive negotiation on the GERD ended today 24th October 2023, in Cairo, Egypt. The next round will be held in December 2023, in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia.

Ethiopia remains committed to reaching a win-win outcome based on the cardinal principle of equitable and reasonable utilization of the Nile River.
